description:
&lt;p&gt;The Northern Care Alliance NHS Group was created by bringing together staff and services from two NHS Trusts, Salford Royal NHS Foundation Trust and The Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust. The sheer size, scale and potential of our combined service is huge. Together, we’ve a wealth of skills and resources to share and tap into and, a wide range of career paths for you to develop and explore. If you want to join a team of over 19,000 NHS experts in delivering high-quality, local care across Salford, Oldham, Bury and Rochdale and beyond – &lt;strong&gt;come and take your place with us. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking to appoint a dynamic Digital Learning Developer who will drive and embed the digital learning agenda across the Northern Care Alliance. Working as part of our award winning Digital Learning Team, the new post holder will design, create and implement digital learning solutions at pace across our portfolio of clinical and talent development programmes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be an accomplished and self-motivated individual with excellent technical, digital and media skills. You will have a keen attention to detail, experienced in content design and a clear understanding of pedagogical learning theories associated with the digital development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have the ability to work under your own initiative with minimal supervision, working to tight and often changing deadlines to improve the educational and learning environment, methodology and outcomes for staff, partners and our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Digital Learning Team is based primarily at Fairfield General Hospital but the post holder will be required to work and travel across all sites within the Northern Care Alliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups and individuals with disabilities are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups. Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All communications to applicants will be via the email address provided on your application form and all further correspondence will be through email, therefore please ensure that you regularly check your emails after the closing date for this post. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul Ladley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Digital Learning Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul.Ladley@pat.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0161 778 2907&lt;/p&gt;
